    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Philada</placeName>
                <date>March 1. 1866</date>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I herewith introduce<lb/> to you <persName>Mr Kronheimer</persName>;
                a gentleman<lb/> who intends to make application<lb/> for the office of Steward of
                the<lb/> Hospital. Having been acquainted<lb/> with him for many years, I can<lb/>
                fully endorse all that he represents<lb/> himself able and willing to do, if<lb/>
                elected to the office. I merely write<lb/> this, for the purposed of stating,
                that<lb/> you may give full credence to all<lb/> he asserts, relative to this
                matter.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Very Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">Michael Hassler</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
